="Edit this page" href="/w/index.php?title=Chain_shift&amp;action=edit"/>\n<link rel="edit" title="Edit this page" href="/w/index.php?title=Chain_shift&amp;action=edit"/>\n<link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/static/apple-touch/wikipedia.png"/>\n<link rel="shortcut icon" href="/static/favicon/wikipedia.ico"/>\n<link rel="search" type="application/opensearchdescription+xml" href="/w/opensearch_desc.php" title="Wikipedia (en)"/>\n<link rel="EditURI" type="application/rsd+xml" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd"/>\n<link rel="license" href="//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/"/>\n<link rel="canonical" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chain_shift"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//login.wikimedia.org"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//meta.wikimedia.org" />\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src="/resources/lib/html5shiv/html5shiv.min.js"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class="mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Chain_shift rootpage-Chain_shift skin-vector action-view">\t\t<div id="mw-page-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="mw-head-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="content" class="mw-body" role="main">\n\t\t\t<a id="top"></a>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteNotice" class="mw-body-content"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="mw-indicators mw-body-content">\n</div>\n\t\t\t<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Chain shift</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="contentSub"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">\n\t\t\t\t\tJump to:\t\t\t\t\t<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, \t\t\t\t\t<a href="#p-search">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><table class="plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Refimprove" role="presentation">\n<tr>\n<td class="mbox-image">\n<div style="width:52px"><a href="/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png" width="50" height="39" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/75px-Question_book-new.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/100px-Question_book-new.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="512" data-file-height="399" /></a></div>\n</td>\n<td class="mbox-text"><span class="mbox-text-span">This article <b>needs additional citations for <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability" title="Wikipedia:Verifiability">verification</a></b>. <span class="hide-when-compact">Please help <a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Chain_shift&amp;action=edit">improve this article</a> by <a href="/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing_with_Wiki_Markup/1" title="Help:Introduction to referencing with Wiki Markup/1">adding citations to reliable sources</a>. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed.</span> <small><i>(July 2010)</i></small> <small class="hide-when-compact"><i>(<a href="/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal" title="Help:Maintenance template removal">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></span></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>In <a href="/wiki/Historical_linguistics" title="Historical linguistics">historical linguistics</a>, a <b>chain shift</b> is a set of <a href="/wiki/Sound_changes" class="mw-redirect" title="Sound changes">sound changes</a> affecting a group of <a href="/wiki/Phonemes" class="mw-redirect" title="Phonemes">phonemes</a>. As the pronunciation of one phoneme changes, other phonemes shift pronunciation as well, often maximizing the difference among phonemes.<sup id="cite_ref-Murray_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Murray-1">[1]</a></sup> The sounds involved in a chain shift can be ordered into a "chain" in such a way that, after the change is complete, each phoneme ends up sounding like what the phoneme before it in the chain sounded like <i>before</i> the change.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources" title="Wikipedia:Citing sources"><span title="This does seem to happen sometimes, but I can\'t find a source suggesting it is necessarily true. (February 2017)">specify</span></a></i>]</sup> The changes making up a chain shift, interpreted as rules of <a href="/wiki/Phonology" title="Phonology">phonology</a>, are in what is termed <i><a href="/wiki/Counterfeeding_order" class="mw-redirect" title="Counterfeeding order">counterfeeding order</a></i>.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="margin-left:0.1em; white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Please_clarify" title="Wikipedia:Please clarify"><span title="The text near this tag may need clarification or removal of jargon. (February 2017)">clarification needed</span></a></i>]</sup></p>\n<p>A well-known example is the <a href="/wiki/Great_Vowel_Shift" title="Great Vowel Shift">Great Vowel Shift</a> in English. The Great Vowel Shift was a chain shift affecting all of the <a href="/wiki/Long_vowel" class="mw-redirect" title="Long vowel">long vowels</a> of <a href="/wiki/Middle_English" title="Middle English">Middle English</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-Fromkin_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Fromkin-2">[2]</a></sup> The changes to the <a href="/wiki/Front_vowel" title="Front vowel">front vowels</a> may be summarized as follows:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">a</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">e:</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">i:</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">a\xc9\xaa</span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>A <b>drag chain</b> or <b>pull chain</b> is a chain shift in which the phoneme at the "leading" edge of the chain changes first. In the example above, the chain shift would be a pull chain if <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/i:/</span> changed to <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/a\xc9\xaa/</span> first, opening up a space at the position of <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[i]</span> which <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/e:/</span> then moved to fill. A <b>push chain</b> is a chain shift in which the phoneme at the "end" of the chain moves first: in this example, if <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/a/</span> moved toward <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[e]</span>, creating a "crowding" effect and causing <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/e:/</span> to move toward <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[i]</span>, and so forth.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (February 2017)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup> It is not known which phonemes changed first during the Great Vowel Shift; many scholars believe the <a href="/wiki/High_vowel" class="mw-redirect" title="High vowel">high vowels</a> such as <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/i:/</span> started the shift, but some suggest that the <a href="/wiki/Low_vowel" class="mw-redirect" title="Low vowel">low vowels</a>, such as <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/a/</span>, may have shifted first.<sup id="cite_ref-Winkler_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Winkler-3">[3]</a></sup></p>\n<p></p>\n<div id="toc" class="toc">\n<div class="toctitle">\n<h2>Contents</h2>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Examples"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Examples</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="#Synchronic_shifts"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Synchronic shifts</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-3"><a href="#See_also"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-4"><a href="#Bibliography"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">Bibliography</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Examples">Examples</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Chain_shift&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Examples">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role="presentation" class="metadata mbox-small selfref noprint" style="background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000;width:22em;">\n<tr>\n<td class="mbox-image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Gnome-speakernotes.svg/40px-Gnome-speakernotes.svg.png" width="40" height="40" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Gnome-speakernotes.svg/60px-Gnome-speakernotes.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Gnome-speakernotes.svg/80px-Gnome-speakernotes.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="128" data-file-height="128" /></td>\n<td class="mbox-text plainlist" style="font-size:95%;"><b>This section includes inline links to audio files.</b> If you have trouble playing the files, see <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Media_help" title="Wikipedia:Media help">Wikipedia Media help</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>A well-known chain shift in the history of English is the <a href="/wiki/Great_Vowel_Shift" title="Great Vowel Shift">Great Vowel Shift</a> of the 15th and 16th centuries. During the Great Vowel Shift all of the long vowels of Middle English, which correspond to <a href="/wiki/Tense_vowel" class="mw-redirect" title="Tense vowel">tense vowels</a> in Modern English, shifted pronunciation. The changes can be summarized as follows:<sup id="cite_ref-Murray_1-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Murray-1">[1]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Fromkin_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Fromkin-2">[2]</a></sup></p>\n<table class="wikitable">\n<caption>Great Vowel Shift</caption>\n<tr>\n<th rowspan="2">Front vowels</th>\n<td><span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Close-mid_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6c/Close-mid_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" class="internal" title="Close-mid front unrounded vowel.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">e\xcb\x90</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Close_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/91/Close_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" class="internal" title="Close front unrounded vowel.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">i:</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:En-us-I.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9f/En-us-I.ogg" class="internal" title="En-us-I.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">a\xc9\xaa</span></a></span></span></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Open-mid_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/71/Open-mid_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" class="internal" title="Open-mid front unrounded vowel.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\x9b:</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Close_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/91/Close_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" class="internal" title="Close front unrounded vowel.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">i:</span></a></span></span></span> <i>or</i> <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Close-mid_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6c/Close-mid_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" class="internal" title="Close-mid front unrounded vowel.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">e\xcb\x90</span></a></span></span></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th rowspan="2">Back vowels</th>\n<td><span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Open-mid_back_rounded_vowel.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/02/Open-mid_back_rounded_vowel.ogg" class="internal" title="Open-mid back rounded vowel.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\x94\xcb\x90</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Close-mid_back_rounded_vowel.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/84/Close-mid_back_rounded_vowel.ogg" class="internal" title="Close-mid back rounded vowel.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">o\xcb\x90</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Close_back_rounded_vowel.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5d/Close_back_rounded_vowel.ogg" class="internal" title="Close back rounded vowel.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">u\xcb\x90</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:En-us-ow.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d1/En-us-ow.ogg" class="internal" title="En-us-ow.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">a\xca\x8a</span></a></span></span></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Open_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/65/Open_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" class="internal" title="Open front unrounded vowel.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">a</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Close-mid_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6c/Close-mid_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg" class="internal" title="Close-mid front unrounded vowel.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">e\xcb\x90</span></a></span></span></span></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>Most vowels shifted to a higher <a href="/wiki/Place_of_articulation" title="Place of articulation">place of articulation</a>, so that the pronunciation of <i>geese</i> changed from <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/ge:s/</span> to <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/gi\xcb\x90s/</span> and <i>broken</i> from <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/br\xc9\x94\xcb\x90ken/</span> to <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/bro\xcb\x90k\xc9\x99n/</span>. The high vowels <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/i\xcb\x90/</span> and <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/u\xcb\x90/</span> became <a href="/wiki/Diphthongs" class="mw-redirect" title="Diphthongs">diphthongs</a> (for example, <i>mice</i> changed from <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:ME-mice.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9c/ME-mice.ogg" class="internal" title="ME-mice.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/mi\xcb\x90s/</span></a></span></span></span> to <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:ModE-mice01.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/97/ModE-mice01.ogg" class="internal" title="ModE-mice01.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/ma\xc9\xaas/</span></a></span></span></span>), and the low back vowel <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/a/</span> was <a href="/wiki/Fronted_(phonetics)" class="mw-redirect" title="Fronted (phonetics)">fronted</a>, causing <i>name</i> to change from <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:ME-name.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e0/ME-name.ogg" class="internal" title="ME-name.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/na:m\xc9\x99/</span></a></span></span></span> to <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:ModE-name.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0e/ModE-name.ogg" class="internal" title="ModE-name.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/ne\xc9\xaam/</span></a></span></span></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-Fromkin_2-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Fromkin-2">[2]</a></sup></p>\n<p>The Great Vowel Shift occurred over centuries, and not all <a href="/wiki/Variety_(linguistics)" title="Variety (linguistics)">varieties</a> of English were affected in the same ways. For example, some speakers in <a href="/wiki/Scotland" title="Scotland">Scotland</a> still pronounce <i>house</i> similarly to its sound in Middle English before the shift, as <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[hus]</span>.<sup id="cite_ref-Winkler_3-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Winkler-3">[3]</a></sup></p>\n<p>A chain shift may affect only one <a href="/wiki/Regional_dialect" class="mw-redirect" title="Regional dialect">regional dialect</a> of a language, or it may begin in a particular regional dialect and then expand beyond the region in which it originated. A number of recent regional chain shifts have occurred in English. Perhaps the most well-known is the <a href="/wiki/Northern_Cities_Vowel_Shift" title="Northern Cities Vowel Shift">Northern Cities Vowel Shift</a>, which is largely confined to the "<a href="/wiki/Inland_Northern_American_English" title="Inland Northern American English">Inland North</a>" region of the United States. Other examples in North America are the <a href="/wiki/California_vowel_shift" class="mw-redirect" title="California vowel shift">California vowel shift</a>, <a href="/wiki/Southern_American_English" title="Southern American English">Southern vowel shift</a> (in the <a href="/wiki/Southern_United_States" title="Southern United States">Southern United States</a>) and the <a href="/wiki/Canadian_Shift" title="Canadian Shift">Canadian Shift</a>. In England, the <a href="/wiki/Cockney" title="Cockney">Cockney</a> vowel shift among working-class Londoners is familiar from its prominence in plays such as <a href="/wiki/George_Bernard_Shaw" title="George Bernard Shaw">George Bernard Shaw</a>\'s <a href="/wiki/Pygmalion_(play)" title="Pygmalion (play)">Pygmalion</a> (and the related musical <a href="/wiki/My_Fair_Lady" title="My Fair Lady">My Fair Lady</a>):<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (February 2017)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup></p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">i\xcb\x90</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ei</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ai</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\x94i</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">oi</span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Many chain shifts are <a href="/wiki/Vowel_shift" title="Vowel shift">vowel shifts</a>, because many sets of vowels are naturally arranged on a multi-value scale (e.g. <a href="/wiki/Vowel_height" class="mw-redirect" title="Vowel height">vowel height</a> or frontness). However, chain shifts can also occur in consonants. A famous example of such a shift is the well-known First Germanic Sound Shift or <a href="/wiki/Grimm%27s_Law" class="mw-redirect" title="Grimm\'s Law">Grimm\'s Law</a>, in which the <a href="/wiki/Proto-Indo-European_language" title="Proto-Indo-European language">Proto-Indo-European</a> <a href="/wiki/Voice_(phonetics)" title="Voice (phonetics)">voiceless</a> <a href="/wiki/Stop_consonant" title="Stop consonant">stop consonants</a> became <a href="/wiki/Fricative" class="mw-redirect" title="Fricative">fricatives</a>, the plain <a href="/wiki/Voiced" class="mw-redirect" title="Voiced">voiced</a> stops became voiceless, and the <a href="/wiki/Breathy_voice" class="mw-redirect" title="Breathy voice">breathy voiced</a> stops became plain voiced:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">b\xca\xb1</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">b</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">p</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">f</span></dd>\n<dd><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">d\xca\xb1</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">d</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">t</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiceless_dental_fricative.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/80/Voiceless_dental_fricative.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiceless dental fricative.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xce\xb8</span></a></span></span></span></dd>\n<dd><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\xa1\xca\xb1</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\xa1</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">k</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">h,x</span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Another is the <a href="/wiki/High_German_consonant_shift" title="High German consonant shift">High German consonant shift</a> which separated <a href="/wiki/Old_High_German" title="Old High German">Old High German</a> from other <a href="/wiki/West_Germanic_languages" title="West Germanic languages">West Germanic dialects</a> such as <a href="/wiki/Old_English" title="Old English">Old English</a>, <a href="/wiki/Old_Frisian" title="Old Frisian">Old Frisian</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Old_Saxon" title="Old Saxon">Old Saxon</a>:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd>\n<table class="wikitable">\n<tr>\n<td><span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiced_alveolar_plosive.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/01/Voiced_alveolar_plosive.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiced alveolar plosive.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">d</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiceless_alveolar_plosive.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/02/Voiceless_alveolar_plosive.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiceless alveolar plosive.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">t</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ts</span>, <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiceless_alveolar_sibilant.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/ac/Voiceless_alveolar_sibilant.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiceless alveolar sibilant.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">s</span></a></span></span></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiced_velar_stop.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/58/Voiced_velar_stop.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiced velar stop.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">g</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiceless_velar_plosive.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e3/Voiceless_velar_plosive.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiceless velar plosive.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">k</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">kx</span>, <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiceless_velar_fricative.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0f/Voiceless_velar_fricative.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiceless velar fricative.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">x</span></a></span></span></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiced_bilabial_plosive.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2c/Voiced_bilabial_plosive.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiced bilabial plosive.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">b</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiceless_bilabial_plosive.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/51/Voiceless_bilabial_plosive.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiceless bilabial plosive.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">p</span></a></span></span></span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">pf</span>, <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiceless_labiodental_fricative.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/33/Voiceless_labiodental_fricative.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiceless labiodental fricative.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">f</span></a></span></span></span></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<p>The Romance languages to the north and west of central Italy (e.g. <a href="/wiki/French_language" title="French language">French</a>, <a href="/wiki/Spanish_language" title="Spanish language">Spanish</a>, <a href="/wiki/Portuguese_language" title="Portuguese language">Portuguese</a>, <a href="/wiki/Catalan_language" title="Catalan language">Catalan</a> and various northern Italian languages) are known for a set of chain shifts collectively termed <i><a href="/wiki/Lenition" title="Lenition">lenition</a></i>, which affected <a href="/wiki/Stop_consonant" title="Stop consonant">stop consonants</a> between vowels:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">pp</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">p</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">b</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiced_bilabial_fricative.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/Voiced_bilabial_fricative.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiced bilabial fricative.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xce\xb2</span></a></span></span></span>, <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">v</span></dd>\n<dd><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">tt</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">t</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">d</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiced_dental_fricative.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6a/Voiced_dental_fricative.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiced dental fricative.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc3\xb0</span></a></span></span></span> (or vanishes)</dd>\n<dd><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">kk</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">k</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\xa1</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span class="nounderlines nowrap"><span class="unicode haudio"><span class="fn"><span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/File:Voiced_velar_fricative.ogg" title="About this sound"><img alt="About this sound" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/17px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/22px-Loudspeaker.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="20" data-file-height="20" /></a>&#160;</span><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/47/Voiced_velar_fricative.ogg" class="internal" title="Voiced velar fricative.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\xa3</span></a></span></span></span>, <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">j</span> (or vanishes)</dd>\n</dl>\n<p>In this case, each sound became weaker (or more "lenited").</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Synchronic_shifts">Synchronic shifts</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Chain_shift&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Synchronic shifts">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>It is also possible for chain shifts to occur synchronically, within the <a href="/wiki/Phonology" title="Phonology">phonology</a> of a language as it exists at a single point in time.<sup id="cite_ref-Kirchner_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Kirchner-4">[4]</a></sup></p>\n<p><a href="/wiki/Nzebi_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Nzebi language">Nzebi</a> (or Njebi), a <a href="/wiki/Bantu_languages" title="Bantu languages">Bantu language</a> of <a href="/wiki/Gabon" title="Gabon">Gabon</a>, has the following chain shift, triggered morphophonologically by certain tense/aspect suffixes:</p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">a</span></td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\x9b</span></td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">e</span></td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">i</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\x99</span></td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">i</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\x94</span></td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">o</span></td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">u</span></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>Examples follow:<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup></p>\n<dl>\n<dd>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<th>Underlying form</th>\n<th>Chain-shifted form</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">sal</span> "to work"</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">sal-i</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">s\xc9\x9bli</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xce\xb2\xc9\x9b\xc9\x9bd</span> "to give"</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xce\xb2\xc9\x9b\xc9\x9bd-i</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xce\xb2eedi</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">bet</span> "to carry"</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">bet-i</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">biti</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">bis</span> "to refuse"</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">bis-i</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">bisi</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">kol\xc9\x99n</span> "to go down"</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">kol\xc9\x99n-i</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">kulini</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">t\xc9\x94\xc9\x94d</span> "to arrive"</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">t\xc9\x94\xc9\x94d-i</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">toodi</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">su\xc9\x9bm</span> "to hide oneself"</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">su\xc9\x9bm-i</span> \xe2\x86\x92 <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">suemi</span></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Another example of a chain from Bedouin Hijazi Arabic involves vowel raising and deletion:<sup id="cite_ref-Kirchner_4-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Kirchner-4">[4]</a></sup></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">a</span></td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">i</span></td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td><i>deletion</i></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>In nonfinal open syllables, <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/a/</span> raises to <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/i/</span> while <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/i/</span> in the same position is deleted.</p>\n<p>Synchronic chain shifts may be circular. An example of this is <a href="/wiki/Amoy_dialect" title="Amoy dialect">Xiamen tone</a> or <a href="/wiki/Taiwanese_Hokkien" title="Taiwanese Hokkien">Taiwanese tone</a> <a href="/wiki/Sandhi" title="Sandhi">sandhi</a>:<sup id="cite_ref-Kirchner_4-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Kirchner-4">[4]</a></sup><sup class="reference" style="white-space:nowrap;">:fn 348</sup><sup class="noprint Inline-Template noprint Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NOTRS" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NOTRS"><span title="This is just a passing mention in a footnote. (February 2017)">better&#160;source&#160;needed</span></a></i>]</sup></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td>53</td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td>44</td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td>22</td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td>21</td>\n<td>\xe2\x86\x92</td>\n<td>53</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>The contour tones are lowered to a lower tone, and the lowest tone (21) circles back to the highest tone (53).</p>\n<p>Synchronic chain shifts are an example of the theoretical problem of <a href="/wiki/Phonological_opacity" title="Phonological opacity">phonological opacity</a>. Although easily accounted for in a derivational rule-based phonology, its analysis in standard parallel <a href="/wiki/Optimality_Theory" title="Optimality Theory">Optimality Theory</a> is problematic.<sup id="cite_ref-Kirchner_4-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Kirchner-4">[4]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Chain_shift&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Isogloss" title="Isogloss">Isogloss</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Sound_change" title="Sound change">Sound change</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Bibliography">Bibliography</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Chain_shift&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Bibliography">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;">\n<div class="mw-references-wrap">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="